          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            @neumi17- I'm all for confidence in your team's ability but that is a ridiculous comment. Bayern with 11 from their best, say 16, players could beat Arsenal (depending on the position(s) of the 2nd choice players) but not with any 11 from their whole squad unless we play as badly as we did against Olympiakos- which, granted, in Europe is possible since our past fails are mental-based. It would take a football "noob" or somebody that hasn't seen the past games between Arsenal and Bayern in recent memory to think that Bayern can turn up with whatever team, play at whatever level and beat another team with world class players who in every game against them have had a period of being on the front foot. Bayern are a terrific team with unrivalled strength-in-depth and are in form but unless Arsenal capitulate, it wont be an easy Bayern win. The bookies agree, the favourite correct score averaged over about 30 betting firms is 1-1, 2nd is a 1-0 Bayern win...
